HEADWORD: Commonly
<hw>Com"mon*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Usually; generally; ordinarily; frequently; for the most part;
<as>as, confirmed habits <ex>commonly</ex> continue through
life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In common; familiarly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commonness</ent>⟦br⟧
